    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix infinite loop in EMM attach restart procedure\n\n### Summary\nThe `emm_proc_attach_restart()` function was creating an infinite loop by calling itself recursively through the EMM state machine. When the state machine received `_EMMREG_ATTACH_INIT`, it was calling `emm_proc_attach_restart()` again instead of initiating the attach procedure directly.\n\nThis fix modifies the state machine handlers to call `emm_proc_attach()` directly with the appropriate attach type, eliminating the recursive loop.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SAP/EmmDeregistered.c`: Replaced recursive call to `emm_proc_attach_restart()` with direct calls to `emm_proc_attach()` with proper attach type determination.\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SAP/EmmDeregisteredAttemptingToAttach.c`: Same fix applied to eliminate recursive loop.\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/SAP/EmmRegisteredInitiated.c`: Same fix applied to eliminate recursive loop.\n- All modified files now include `emm_proc_defs.h` for attach type constants.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Trigger an attach restart scenario (e.g., timer T3402 or T3411 expiration)\n2. Call `emm_proc_attach_restart()` \n3. Observe infinite recursion as the function calls itself through the state machine\n4. System will eventually crash with stack overflow\n\nThe fix ensures that when `emm_proc_attach_restart()` is called, the state machine transitions to the appropriate state and then initiates the attach procedure directly without creating a recursive loop.\n"
}